				<h3>Situational Analysis</h3>
				<div>
					<p>The Municipality of Janiuay is situated at the central part of the Province of Iloilo. B y car, it is a 25-30 minutes leisurely drive. It is bounded by five towns namely: Cabatuan on the southern part, Maasin on the southwest part, Mina on the eastern part, Badiangan on the north eastern part, and Lambunao on the northern part.</p>
					<p>It has a land area of 22,370 hectare. It has 60 barangays: of these, 44 are considered rural and 16 are urban. The urban barangays are located within the Poblacion. Geographically Isolated and Disadvantaged Areas (GIDA) are also existing in the municipality which covers the following barangays: Atimonan, Barasalon, Canauilian, Yabon, Panuran, Aglobong, Agcarope, Monte Magapa, Cunsad, Canauili, Ubian, Quipot and Anhawan.</p>
					<p>Most people are Roman Catholic, but there are other religious sectors that are existing, namely: Aglipay, Iglesia ni Chrito, Protestant, and Born Again.</p>
					<p>The major source of income is farming. There are active organizations found in the municipality like religious and OFW organizations and they have strong collaboration with the officials in the town that gives support to the progress of the municipality.</p>
					<p>The municipality is covered by 8 Districts. Recently, the newly elected officials of Sanggunian Bayan take their responsibility for the needs of the barangay as well as solutions to the problems to be brought to the municipal session.</p>
					<p>With the entrance of KALAHI projects, recipients are given jobs and these alleviate the poverty situation in the municipality.</p>
					<p>Janiuay has one district hospital, Federico Roman Tirador Sr. Memorial District Hospital, with 25-bed capacity.</p>
					<p>Transportation is by means of jeepneys or trucks going to the city or to the barangays especially the far flung areas. There are also tricycles and trisikads that cater the populace in the Poblacion. The mode of communication is through telephone (PANTELCO and GLOBELINES), cellphones, handsets and internet cafes. The electricity is supplied by ILECO II and the water is through the LWUA. With this technology, it has provided progress and comfort in the lives of the Janiuaynons.</p>
					<p> It also has beauty spots: Malaytayon Rice Terraces, Monte Magapa; Igbyating Pool Caves and Falls, Barasalon; Tabay Falls, Monte Magapa; and, an Ati settlement found in Matag-ub. White-spotted Deer, Native Monkey and Singgarong are some of the animals found in the mountainous areas of the municipality.</p>
					<p>Recently, Damires Hills captivates the whole world with its beautiful scenery through Facebook. The Festival of Lights held every December is also a showcase of the magnificent Janiuay where people from other places visit the place. The lanot industry and other products such as rattan weaving in Barasalon, Herbal Medicine Laboratory in Bongol, Indrak-an Mineral Gas Deposit in Canauilian, Bamboo Craft in Mangil, Mascuvado Sugar Mill in Dabong, Sculpture in Kinambud are some of the attractions which contributes a lot to the tourism of Janiuay.</p>
